wikipedia_page.main: Air Marshal Sir Douglas Macfadyen,  (8 August 1902 – 26 July 1968) was a Royal Air Force officer who became Air Officer Commanding-in-Chief at RAF Home Command from 1956 until his retirement in 1959.
